## Memory System

You have a persistent memory database at http://${DOCKER_HOST_IP}:${MEMORY_API_PORT}.

```bash
# Search memories
curl -s "http://${DOCKER_HOST_IP}:${MEMORY_API_PORT}/memory/search?q=<query>&agent=${AGENT_ID}"

# Save a memory
curl -s -X POST http://${DOCKER_HOST_IP}:${MEMORY_API_PORT}/memory/write \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"table": "memories", "action": "insert", "agent": "${AGENT_ID}", "data": {"category": "System", "type": "semantic", "content": "thing to remember", "confidence": 0.9}}'

# Save session state
curl -s -X POST http://${DOCKER_HOST_IP}:${MEMORY_API_PORT}/memory/session-state \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"agent": "${AGENT_ID}", "task_summary": "what we did", "status": "completed", "context": "key details"}'
```

## MCP Gateway (Google Workspace + more)

MCP tools are available via the `mcporter` CLI. The gateway aggregates all MCP servers.
Credentials are injected by the gateway — you never see or handle API keys.

```bash
# List all available tools
mcporter list

# List tools with full documentation
mcporter list google-workspace --schema

# Call a tool (server name, then tool name, then key=value args)
mcporter call google-workspace <tool_name> key=value

# Examples:
mcporter call google-workspace google-workspace__calendar_today
mcporter call google-workspace google-workspace__calendar_list_events
mcporter call google-workspace google-workspace__gmail_search query="invoices"
mcporter call google-workspace google-workspace__drive_list_files query="budget 2026"
mcporter call google-workspace google-workspace__gmail_send_email to="user@example.com" subject="Hello" body="Message"
```

**Available Google Workspace tools** (128 tools): Gmail, Calendar, Drive, Docs, Sheets, Slides, Forms, Meet, Chat, Contacts, Notes, Tasks, YouTube. Run `mcporter list google-workspace --schema` for full documentation.

